Angola  plans to lower duties and
taxes on 13 basic food items in 2012 to make them more
affordable, Radio Nacional de Angola said, citing Mario Pires,
coordinator of the Angolaâ€™s Tax Reform Project.  Customs duties, port tariffs and consumption taxes on
products such as rice, sugar, beans and powdered milk will be
lowered or removed, Pires said, according to the radio station.  To contact the reporter on this story:
